<SLUG> BC-ADD-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by New York Times News Service clients) 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, March 12. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
BORDER _ A customs officer sent to check a pre-dawn border alarm at
a remote desert crossing this week found himself ducking gunfire
from a Mexican military unit he says had crossed into Arizona. Rob
Daniels, a spokesman for the Border Patrol's Tucson sector, said
U.S. law enforcement agencies increasingly suspect that some of the
crossings occur not because traffickers are being chased, but
because they are being protected. By DENNIS WAGNER. Story will move
in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
DOLE (PARADISE VALLEY, Ariz.) _ Elizabeth Dole accomplished what
she set out to do in Arizona on Thursday: glad-hand a few politicos
and make important contacts but avoid answering any real questions
about her campaign. By CHRIS MOESER. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
