<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-ISMAIL-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AGENT SAYS ISMAIL PLANS TO MAKE DECISION SUNDAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN LYONS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Raghib ``Rocket'' Ismail is expected to make a
decision Sunday night about whether he will sign a contract to play
wide receiver with the Cowboys, Ismail's agent said yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's going to let me know on Sunday and then we'll let the
world know,'' Jack Mula, Ismail's representative, said.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys have already offered Ismail a contract, said Mula,
who would not give the specifics of the terms. Ismail, 29, is also
considering a return to play with the Carolina Panthers, where he
enjoyed his best season as a pro in 1998 with 69 receptions for
1,074 yards and eight touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   Ismail visited with Cowboys officials last week. The Cowboys
have said they would like to add a receiver with Ismail's speed to
the lineup. They wouldn't comment specifically on the negotiations.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys are waiting on Ismail's decision before making other
moves. Restricted free-agent wide receiver Pat Jeffers has drawn
interest from the St. Louis Rams, making a visit earlier this week.
The Rams would have to give up a fifth-round draft choice to sign
Jeffers, although Jeffers' agent, Brad Blank, said the Rams told
him they may try to trade for Jeffers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now, though, the Rams are just waiting to see what the
Cowboys do with \RIsmail\S,'' Blank said. ``If they sign him, that
will leave them without a whole lot of money under the salary cap
to match any offer the Rams might make toward Jeffers.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys must also decide if they are going to sign
free-agent linebacker Quentin Coryatt.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the Cowboys re-signed yesterday linebacker Nate
Hemsley, quarterback Mike Quinn and linebacker Brandon Tolbert.
None played much last season.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
