<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories for use
Sunday, March 14 or thereafter
</P>
<P>
   CABLE SERVICES
</P>
<P>
   Cable companies nationwide offer different packages of channels
and services. Here is a basic run-down on service categories and
regulatory status:
</P>
<P>
   Basic service: Usually includes local broadcast channels and a
few cable channels. Remains regulated.
</P>
<P>
   Expanded basic service: Typically has some 30 channels,
including favorites such as CNN, TNT, ESPN and Discovery. Becomes
unregulated March 31.
</P>
<P>
   Premium service: Usually includes additional movie and sports
channels as well as pay-for-view programming. Never regulated.
</P>
<P>
   Advanced digital service: Not widely available yet. Two-way
interactive systems to offer hundreds of new channels, high-speed
Internet access and telephone service. Never regulated.
</P>
<P>
   Source: Federal Communications Commission, staff research
</P>
