 &HT;    BIOGRAPHICAL INFORMATION FOR MANUEL BARTLETT DIAZ
 &HT;    With MEXICO-BARTLETT-$ADV14.
 &HT;    For Use Sun., March 14 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By SUSAN FERRISS 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANUEL BARTLETT DIAZ: A ``DINOSAUR'' RUNS FOR PRESIDENT OF
MEXICO
</P>
<P>
   AGE: 61
</P>
<P>
   PARTY: Revolutionary Institutional Party (PRI), which has
controlled Mexico's presidency since 1929.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICAL HISTORY: Governor of Puebla state (1993-Feb. 99),
where Mexico's giant Volkswagen auto assembly plant is based.
</P>
<P>
   Secretary of the Interior (1982-88), a powerful cabinet position
that put Bartlett in charge of elections. Disgruntled Mexicans
accuse him of fraud in 1988 presidential election, a rumor he
denies.
</P>
<P>
   Has also has served as Mexico's Secretary of Public Education,
Assistant Budget Secretary, Director of Political Affairs for the
Foreign Ministry, Secretary General of the PRI's Executive
Committee and coordinator of the PRI's presidential campaign during
the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
   ACADEMIC HISTORY: Studied law and political science at the
National Autonomous University of Mexico; and law at the University
of Paris. Also studied public administration at Victoria University
in Manchester, England.
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY:
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
