<SLUG> BC-COMPUTER-HOTLIST-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMPUTER HOTLIST: TALK RADIO 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By DWIGHT SILVERMAN 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Talk radio is often painted as a place where the average
American can go to express his or her views.
</P>
<P>
   Whether that's accurate or not is a matter of debate, but here
are some sites:
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Laura Schlessinger _ www.drlaura.com/
</P>
<P>
   Whether you think America's favorite talk-show shrink is a
mean-spirited shrew or blessed with common-sense wisdom, you'll
enjoy her slickly designed Web site. Browse her photo album, listen
to samples of her show and learn about the books she's published. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Fresh Air _ www.whyy.org/freshair/
</P>
<P>
   Looking for something a little higher-brow? While Fresh Air host
Terry Gross doesn't take calls, her interviews with writers,
actors, directors, musicians and occasionally politicians are among
the most intelligent _ and still accessible _ you'll find
anywhere. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Talkers Magazine's Talk Daily _ www.talkers.com/daily.html
</P>
<P>
   Talkers Magazine, which is devoted to the talk-show industry,
posts a daily, transcripted roundup of some of the more interesting
exchanges and monologues heard around the nation. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Broadcast.com: Talk Radio _ www.broadcast.com/radio/Talk/
</P>
<P>
   Although there are plenty of national big names in talk radio,
some of the most interesting work is at the grass-roots level.
Broadcast.com links to talk-show format radio stations all over the
country. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Talkspot _ www.talkspot.com/
</P>
<P>
   Talkspot is a Web-based talk-show network that consists of three
``channels'' _ news and politics, life and explorations and
``Channel Z,'' which features pop culture and the offbeat. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Bruce Williams _ www.brucewilliams.com/
</P>
<P>
   Bruce Williams offers advice on all the ``grown-up'' aspects of
life, ranging from doing battle with a neighbor over deed
restrictions to figuring out whether to buy or start a business.
Although you cannot listen to his show at his site, you can learn
about his history and even sign up to take a cruise with him. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Art Bell _ www.artbell.com
</P>
<P>
   Late-night talk show host Art Bell tackles topics that are too
weird to even be an X-Files episode. And if you think he's strange,
wait 'til you hear his callers! Broadcasting from the desert in
Nevada, Bell is the ultimate conspiracy theorist and his Web site
reflects his offbeat point of view.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
