<HEADLINE>
WHO APPOINTED THE APPOINTERS OF KENNETH STARR?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: In an earlier column, you said that a three-judge panel
appointed Kenneth Starr. Who appointed the three judges? _ A.R.,
Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: The three judges on the panel, also called the Special
Division, were appointed by the chief justice of the United States,
William Rehnquist, in accordance with the terms of the Independent
Counsel Law.
</P>
<P>
   The law created the Special Division and made it part of the
U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia. The chief
justice must choose current or retired federal appellate court
judges, and one must come from the D.C. Court of Appeals. They
serve two-year terms and can be reappointed.
</P>
<P>
   The judges who appointed Starr were presiding Judges David
Sentelle of the D.C. court, John Butzner Jr. of the 4th Circuit and
Joseph Sneed of the 9th Circuit.
</P>
<P>
   The Special Division, which meets privately, now has these
members: Sentelle, Peter Fay of the 11th Circuit in Atlanta and
Richard Cudahy of the 7th Circuit in Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   Sentelle was criticized in 1994 for having lunch with Republican
Sens. Jesse Helms and Lauch Faircloth three weeks before Starr's
appointment. The judge said that ``to the best of my recollection''
the issue of an upcoming counsel appointment was not discussed.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I'm looking for the computer game Hoyle Bridge &AMP; Euchre by
Sierra On-Line, but I can only find it in CD-ROM format. Where can
I find it on floppy disk? _ L.L., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: A Sierra representative said that the current version of the
game is only on CD.
</P>
<P>
   More than a dozen bridge programs are available from Baron
Barclay, a company that bills itself as ``the world's largest
bridge supply company.'' To request the company's 64-page catalog,
call (800) 274-2221 or write to Baron Barclay Bridge Supplies, 3600
Chamberlain Lane, No. 230, Louisville, KY 40241.
</P>
<P>
   You can contact Sierra by calling (800) 757-7707 or visiting the
World Wide Web site www.sierra.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Catherine Zeta-Jones? _ D.C., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to the ``Mask of Zorro'' star in care of International
Creative Management, 8942 Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, CA 90211.
</P>
<P>
   Zeta-Jones, 29, will be appearing with Sean Connery in the film
``Entrapment,'' due out April 30.
</P>
<P>
   A native of Swansea, Wales, Zeta-Jones had her first starring
role in the British TV series ``The Darling Buds of May'' in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) .MDBU/ nn
</P>
</TEXT>
