<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At midday, the industrial average was down
16 points, or 0.2 percent, at 9,880. The Nasdaq index was off 46
points, or 1.9 percent. Elsewhere, shares jumped more than 5
percent in Frankfurt because of the Lafontaine resignation.
London's market was down 0.7 percent, following Wall Street.
Brazilian stocks were off 1.7 percent, and Mexican stocks were
little changed. Overnight, prices were flat in Tokyo and up 1.3
percent in Hong Kong. On the American debt market, the long bond
was up 7/32 point, with the yield at 5.55 percent.
</P>
