   CANADA-MAGAZINES (Toronto) _ Canada's House of Commons may vote
today to approve legislation that would ban Canadians from
advertising in ``split-run'' magazines, which are sold as the
Canadian editions of American magazines but have little Canadian
elements. Canada's last attempt to ban split-runs was struck down
by the WTO. The U.S. is threatening to impose trade sanctions and
Canada is threatening counter-sanctions. By Kalyani Vittala.
</P>
