<P>
   BOX-FIGHT-PRELIM _ NEW YORK _ Before Evander Holyfield attempts
to win his third world title belt, Sam Garr will be seeking his
first. Garr, who fights out of the Biggs-Morrison Gym in Atlanta,
meets WBA welterweight champion James Page on the undercard of the
Holyfield-Lennox Lewis heavyweight unification. Garr (27-2), who
has been predominantly a club fighter in the Atlanta area, has held
belts of lesser sanctioning bodies, but this is his first shot at a
title from one of the big three (WBA, WBC, IBF). (Schultz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
