<P>
   TV-COLUMN (Undated) _ So here's the setup: Woman is happily
married. Or so she thinks. Husband, a grade-school principal and a
real slice o' slime, is having an affair. Husband leaves her, and
now it's time to pick up the pieces. It may be impossible to get an
accurate count of how often this plot line has been used in a film.
Whatever the score, add ``Replacing Dad'' (CBS 9 p.m. Sunday) to
the list. But not the A list.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
