WOMANPILOT (Chino Valley, Ariz.) - Irene Leverton of Chino Valley
was one of a handful of women who in the 1960s almost became the
first female astronauts but NASA denied that opportunity to the
women who later became known as the ``Mercury 13.'' Flying has been
her life. She never married because it would have interfered with
her flying. On her walls in her trailer are pictures of her planes
_ those she has flown over the years. She is an Arizona character.
By MAUREEN WEST. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
