Jackson has warned the Navajo Nation that the number of medicine
men on the nation's largest reservation is dwindling and some
ceremonies are in danger of being lost forever. Now, as the tribe
is in the midst of a pilot program that attracted more than 300
applicants and provides stipends for young Navajos, Jackson and
others are wondering if it's too little, too late. By BILL DONOVAN.
