<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Then and now: A few years makes a lot of difference
 &HT;    By Gary Borders
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   NACOGDOCHES, Texas _ Here are some sure signs that we Baby
Boomers are getting old, courtesy of e-mail from friends who should
be working instead of sending this stuff around:
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Being caught with Hustler magazine. Now: Being caught by
Hustler magazine.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Getting out to a new, hip joint. Now: Getting a new hip
joint.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Moving to California because it's cool. Now: Moving to
California because it's warm.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Killer weed. Now: Weed killer.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Being called into the principal's office. Now: Storming
into the principal's office.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Long hair. Now: Longing for hair.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: The Grateful Dead. Now: Dr. Kevorkian.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Worrying about nobody coming to your party. Now:
Worrying about nobody coming to your funeral.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Watching John Glenn's historic space flight with your
parents. Now: Watching John Glenn's historic space flight with your
kids.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Passing the driving test. Now: Passing the vision test.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: The president's struggle with Fidel. Now: The
president's struggle with fidelity.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Trying to look like Marlon Brando or Elizabeth Taylor.
Now: Trying not to look like Marlon Brando or Elizabeth Taylor.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Elvis in the Army. Now: Elvis in a UFO.
</P>
<P>
   _ Then: Keg. Now: EKG
</P>
<P>
   Don't shoot me, I'm just the messenger. And now, for the women
out there, here's a collection of men jokes. This is your way to
get even for all those dumb blonde jokes men love to tell.
</P>
<P>
   _ How many honest, intelligent, caring men in the world does it
take to do the dishes? Both of them.
</P>
<P>
   _ Why does it take 1 million sperm to fertilize one egg? They
won't stop to ask directions.
</P>
<P>
   _ Why are blonde jokes so short? So men can remember them.
</P>
<P>
   _ What do you call a woman who knows where her husband is every
night? A widow.
</P>
<P>
   _ How do you get a man to do sit-ups? Put the remote control
between his toes.
</P>
<P>
   _ What did God say after creating Adam? Surely I can do better
than that.
</P>
<P>
   _ How many men does it take to change a roll of toilet paper?
Nobody knows. It's never happened.
</P>
<P>
   _ How does a man show that he is planning for the future? He
buys two cases of beer.
</P>
<P>
   One last joke, and then I'll stop. Honest.
</P>
<P>
   A man was walking along a California beach and stumbled across
an old lamp. He picked it up, rubbed it, and out popped a genie.
The genie wasn't in a good mood.
</P>
<P>
   ``OK, you released me from the lamp, yadda, yadda, yadda. This
is the fourth time this month, and I'm getting a little sick of
these wishes. I'm just giving you one wish, not three.''
</P>
<P>
   The man thought about it a while.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've always wanted to go to Hawaii,'' he said, ``But I'm
scared to fly, and I get very seasick. Could you build me a bridge
to Hawaii so I can drive over there?''
</P>
<P>
   The genie laughed. ``Are you nuts? Think of the logistics.
Imagine trying to get the pilings all the way to the bottom of the
Pacific. Think of all that concrete and steel. There's no way.
You'll have to come up with another wish.''
</P>
<P>
   The man thought a while longer.
</P>
<P>
   ``OK, I've been married and divorced four times. All my ex-wives
say I'm insensitive and I don't understand women. So my wish is
that I could understand women, know how they really feel inside and
what they're thinking.''
</P>
<P>
   The genie said, ``You want that bridge two-lane or four-lane?''
</P>
<P>
   Gary Borders is editor and publisher of The Nacogdoches Daily
Sentinel. His e-mail address is gborders(at)coxnews.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
