AOL in a stock deal worth more than $8 billion. The deal, cleared
Friday by the Justice Department, would catapult AOL into new
business markets and solidify its position as a major player in
online advertising and electronic commerce. (Rick McKay/Cox News
Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) STERLING, Va. -- March 12, 1999 -- AOL-COX-1, 3-12 --
Technicians monitor AOL's system in the company's Networks
Operations Center in Sterling. On Wednesday, Netscape shareholders
are expected to approve the sale of their company to AOL in a stock
deal worth more than $8 billion. The deal, cleared Friday by the
