<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OBIT-WEISMAN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HERMAN WEISMAN, LEADER IN ZIONIST GROUPS, DIES AT 95  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Fla., Ala.)   By ERIC PACE    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Herman L. Weisman, a lawyer who was prominent in American
Zionist organizations, died on Sunday at the Hospice of Palm Beach
County, Fla. He was 95 and lived in Palm Beach County.
</P>
<P>
   Weisman was president of the Zionist Organization of America
from 1970 to 1974, at a time when it had 110,000 members. His
earlier posts included chairman of the American Zionist Fund in the
mid-1950s, chairman of the Zionist Organization of America's
national executive committee from 1965 to 1969, and chairman of
that organization's national administrative board in 1969 and 1970.
He was also active in other Jewish organizations.
</P>
<P>
   In the 1920s and '30s, he held New York state prosecutorial
positions, and from 1938 to 1940, he was legal assistant to John
Harlan Amen, the special assistant state attorney general, in
Amen's investigation of law enforcement in Brooklyn. Weisman was
active in the prosecution of Alexander R. Baldwin, staff assistant
to District Attorney William F.X. Geoghan of Brooklyn. Baldwin was
acquitted of a bribery charge in 1939, but his license to practice
law was later revoked.
</P>
<P>
   Weisman was born in Russia but was brought to New York as an
infant in 1906. He received a bachelor's degree magna cum laude in
1924 from City College, where he was a captain of the debating
team, and his law degree in 1927 from Harvard University.
</P>
<P>
   During the time he had a private law practice in New York, he
counted Eleanor Roosevelt among his clients.
</P>
<P>
   Weisman is survived by his wife, Jeannette Cobey Weisman of West
Palm Beach, Fla.; three sons, Edward, of North Palm Beach, Fla.,
Robert, of Lantana, Fla., and Matthew, of Weston, Mass.; a sister,
Nettie Kramer of Birmingham, Ala.; eight grandchildren; and four
great-grandchildren.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-12-99 2207EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
